body:
ocicrypt_keyprovider.conf is as follows:

```
{
        "key-providers": {
                "enc": {
                    "grpc": "127.0.0.1:1234"
                },
                "dec": {
                    "grpc": "127.0.0.1:4321"
                }
        }
}
```

The container image was successfully encrypted using the following command:

```
OCICRYPT_KEYPROVIDER_CONFIG=/etc/containerd/ocicrypt/ocicrypt_keyprovider.conf skopeo copy --encryption-key --provider:enc oci:example oci:example-enc
```

When attempting to decrypt the container image with the following command:

```
OCICRYPT_KEYPROVIDER_CONFIG=/etc/containerd/ocicrypt/ocicrypt_keyprovider.conf skopeo copy --decryption-key --provider:dec oci:example-enc oci:example
```

It will fail. After investigation, we found that `dec` in `--decryption-key --provider:dec` is not parsed, skopeo will still look for the keyprovider named "enc" to obtain the key, that is, if we change the ocicrypt_keyprovider.conf to the following:

```
{
        "key-providers": {
                "enc": {
                    "grpc": "127.0.0.1:4321"
                }
        }
}
```

At this time, the decryption can be successful, which means that when skopeo uses keyprovider for encryption and decryption, keyprovider programs with different names are not supported for encryption and decryption, this means that the --decryption-key parameter is not resolved during decryption.

